NAME
    diff - compare files line by line

SYNOPSIS
    diff [options] <file1> <file2>

DESCRIPTION
    Compares two files line by line and outputs the differences.
    Returns 0 if identical, 1 if different, 2 on error.

OPTIONS
    -u              Unified format (default)
    -c              Context format
    -y              Side-by-side format
    -q              Report only whether files differ
    -s              Report when files are identical
    -i              Ignore case differences
    -w              Ignore all whitespace
    -b              Ignore changes in whitespace amount
    -B              Ignore blank lines
    -U <n>          Lines of context (default 3)
    --no-color      Disable colored output

OUTPUT FORMAT
    Unified format shows changes with context:
        --- file1
        +++ file2
        @@ -start,count +start,count @@
        (space)  unchanged line
        -        removed line
        +        added line

    Side-by-side shows files in columns:
        left line         right line
        left line    <    (removed)
                     >    right line

EXAMPLES
    diff file1.txt file2.txt
        Compare two files

    diff -u old.txt new.txt
        Unified diff format

    diff -q config1 config2
        Just report if different

    diff -i file1 file2
        Ignore case differences

    diff -w a.txt b.txt
        Ignore whitespace

    diff -y file1 file2
        Side-by-side comparison

    diff -U5 old new
        Show 5 lines of context

EXIT STATUS
    0       Files are identical
    1       Files are different
    2       Error occurred

SEE ALSO
    cat, cmp
